--></style></head><body lang=FR-CA link=blue vlink="#954F72" style='word-wrap:break-word'><div class=WordSection1><p class=MsoNormal>Bonjour</p><p class=MsoNormal>J’ai un sommaire des demandes de Maria qui demandent votre autorisation.</p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>Vacation, congé, sick et une proposition pour severance.</p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>On pourra en discuter. Cela va un peu guider le contrat pour Andres.</p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>Le premier contrat est toujours le plus long!! Once we have it, we are good to go!<span lang=EN-CA><o:p></o:p></span></p><p style='margin-bottom:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><u><span lang=EN-CA>SOMMAIRE CONTRAT MARIA PEREZ MAROM:</span></u></b><span lang=EN-CA><o:p></o:p></span></p><ol start=1 type=1><li style='margin-bottom:0cm;line-height:normal;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1'><span lang=EN-CA>Yearly bonus: Not yet. Will be developped later- Je vais confirmer dans le document de retour a Maria.<o:p></o:p></span></li></ol><p style='mso-margin-top-alt:5.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:0cm;margin-left:36.0pt;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-CA><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><ol start=2 type=1><li style='margin-bottom:0cm;line-height:normal;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1'><span lang=EN-CA>Vacation: Maria a indiqué 6 semaines. On confirme 4 semaines ou vous avez eu des discussions pour 6 semaines de vacances?<o:p></o:p></span></li></ol><p style='mso-margin-top-alt:5.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:0cm;margin-left:36.0pt;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-CA><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><ol start=3 type=1><li style='margin-bottom:0cm;line-height:normal;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1'><span lang=EN-CA>Congé statutaires: Maria a indiqué 11 jours de congé et nous n’avons que 8 jours pour le québec. Les jours de congé demandés ne sont pas usuels pour les petitess entreprises aux USA.<o:p></o:p></span></li></ol><p style='mso-margin-top-alt:5.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:0cm;margin-left:36.0pt;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-CA>Je suggère d’aller à 9 et de donner une journée de plus pour le Québec. <o:p></o:p></span></p><ol start=4 type=1><li style='margin-bottom:0cm;line-height:normal;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1'><span lang=EN-CA>Sick days: Maria is asking for 15 sick days (3 weeks) Florida laws = 0 and Quebec mininum = 2<o:p></o:p></span></li></ol><p style='mso-margin-top-alt:5.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:0cm;margin-left:36.0pt;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-CA>I suggest to increase the days for quebec in order to align to a best employer which would be closer to 10 days a year. No impact on cash flow for company (no one is being replaced) That would also help her with the decrease in vacation.<o:p></o:p></span></p><ol start=5 type=1><li style='margin-bottom:0cm;line-height:normal;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1'><span lang=EN-CA>Severance agreement: Maria is asking for 2 years, in case the business is not picking up and decides to close. This is not reasonnable. For the safety of the business, i would suggest a small severance agreement that would secure her and prevent her to leave quickly if she sees the business not going well and accelerate the negative impact on the business. <o:p></o:p></span></li></ol><p style='mso-margin-top-alt:5.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:0cm;margin-left:36.0pt;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-CA>I would suggest 8 weeks to 12 weeks severance- This would be the time it takes her to find alternate employment.<o:p></o:p></span></p><ol start=6 type=1><li style='margin-bottom:0cm;line-height:normal;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1'><span lang=EN-CA>Non compete clause: I rewrote the non compete clause as i did not feel HR Business support was well protected with it. It is listed below...<o:p></o:p></span></li></ol><p style='margin-bottom:0cm;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-CA><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p style='margin-bottom:0cm;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-CA>Let me know what you think!<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style='margin-bottom:0cm;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-CA><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p style='margin-bottom:0cm;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-CA>Not sure why i switch to english!<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style='margin-bottom:0cm;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-CA><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p style='margin-bottom:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><u><span lang=EN-CA>Maria’s suggestion of non compete clause:</span></u></b><span lang=EN-CA><o:p></o:p></span></p><p style='margin-bottom:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=EN-CA>Non-Competition Clauses</span></b><span lang=EN-CA><o:p></o:p></span></p><p style='margin-bottom:0cm;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-CA>While employee is in the service of HR Business Support and for a period of three (3) months following the termination of her employment, for any reason, except for termination of employment at the initiative of the company, employee will not compete with the company; meaning, will not to invest, get involved or offer services in similar capacity while employed with HR Business Support who <span style='color:black;background:white'>specializes in human resources solutions for businesses</span> as noted in Exhibit A. <o:p></o:p></span></p><p style='margin-bottom:0cm;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-CA><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p style='margin-bottom:0cm;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-CA>My proposal- using something from my past:<o:p></o:p></span></p><ol start=1 type=A><li style='mso-list:l0 level1 lfo2'><i><span lang=EN-CA>Scope of Non-Competition: During the term of employment and for a period of 12 months following the termination of employment, the HR Director shall not engage in any activity or employment, either directly or indirectly, that competes with the business interests of the Company within the state of Florida, USA.</span></i><span lang=EN-CA><o:p></o:p></span></li><li style='mso-list:l0 level1 lfo2'><i><span lang=EN-CA>Prohibited Activities: The HR Director shall not, directly or indirectly, engage in or provide services to any business or organization that is similar to or in direct competition with the Company's HR-related activities, including but not limited to recruitment, training and development, compensation and benefits management, employee relations, and HR strategy formulation.</span></i><span lang=EN-CA><o:p></o:p></span></li><li style='margin-bottom:0cm;line-height:normal;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo2'><span lang=EN-CA>F<i>urthermore, understanding the employee is a seasoned human resource professional and her only way of making a living is providing human resources expertise, HR Business Support will not interfere in employee continuing to provide human resource services to prospect employers who do not compete with HR Business Support.</i><o:p></o:p></span></li><li style='mso-list:l0 level1 lfo2'><i><span lang=EN-CA>Geographic Limitation: The non-competition restriction applies only within the state of Florida, USA, where the Company conducts its business operations or has a substantial presence.</span></i><span lang=EN-CA><o:p></o:p></span></li><li style='mso-list:l0 level1 lfo2'><i><span lang=EN-CA>Exception: This non-competition clause shall not apply if the HR Director obtains prior written consent from the Company's authorized

